Hello!

I have a three monitor setup, two of which support DDC/CI, however 
neither are in the database. Namely, the Asus VH203T and Dell U2312HM. 
I've attached the logs, with i2c5 being the Asus and i2c6 being the Dell.

Worth noting, however, is the weird interaction I've gotten with the 
Dell. For whatever reason, on boot it shows fine in GDDCControl, and the 
brightness/contrast sliders work fine (haven't toyed with the others 
yet). However, running 'sudo LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol dev:/dev/i2c-6 -c 
-d' would print what you can see in the output file, and would also lag 
the terminal until i killed it.

Also worth mentioning, is like above, I used dev:/dev/i2c-X instead of 
-p; -p was only outputting the information for the Asus monitor. I don't 
think this would make any difference, but it's worth mentioning any 
variables.


